-- Buenos Aires Seeks $216 Million Loan From Brazil, Cronista Says
-- B y   P a b l o   G o n z a l e z
-- 2012-08-21T12:45:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-21/buenos-aires-seeks-216-million-loan-from-brazil-cronista-says.html
The city of  Buenos Aires  is seeking
approval from the local legislature to take a loan of about $216
million from Brazil’s development bank BNDES to acquire 120 new
subway cars, newspaper El Cronista said.  The city will acquire the rolling stock from Alstom Brasil
Energia e Transporte Ltda., the Buenos Aires-based newspaper
cited Rogelio Frigerio, the president of the city legislature’s
budget commission, as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pablo Gonzalez in Buenos Aires at 
 pgonzalez49@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Attwood at 
 jattwood3@bloomberg.net  